# ── StudentMarket environment variable template ───────────────────────────────
# Commit this file. It documents which vars the app needs.
# Put your actual values in .env.local (gitignored, never committed).
#
# LESSON: .env vs .env.local
#   .env        → committed, empty/safe defaults, acts as documentation
#   .env.local  → gitignored, holds real secrets and local overrides
#
# Copy this file to get started:
#   cp .env .env.local
# Then fill in your real values in .env.local.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Base URL of your backend API.
# Leave empty to use mock data (no backend needed during development).
#
# LESSON: Use your Mac's LAN IP — NOT localhost.
# The phone is a separate device. "localhost" on the phone points to itself.
# Find your Mac's IP: System Settings → Wi-Fi → Details → IP Address
#
# Example: API_URL=http://192.168.0.190:3000
API_URL=
